following holds:

\begin{align*}
v_1x_1 + v_2x_2 + v_3x_3 + v_4x_4 = b
\end{align*}

Write this in matrix notation and then follow the steps from part (a).

statement_latex:
Consider the vectors

\begin{align*}
v_1 = \left(\begin{array}{c}
1/2 \\ 1/2 \\ 1/2 \\ 1/2
\end{array}\right), \quad 
v_2 = \left(\begin{array}{c}
1/2 \\ 1/2 \\ -1/2 \\ -1/2
\end{array}\right),
\end{align*}

\begin{align*}
v_3 = \left(\begin{array}{c}
1/2 \\ -1/2 \\ 1/2 \\ -1/2
\end{array}\right), \quad 
v_4 = \left(\begin{array}{c}
1/2 \\ -1/2 \\ -1/2 \\ 1/2
\end{array}\right)
\end{align*}

\textbf{b)} Let \emph{b = (1,2,3,4)\textsuperscript{T}}. Then write
\emph{b} as a linear combination of the vectors
\emph{v\textsubscript{1}, v\textsubscript{2}, v\textsubscript{3},
v\textsubscript{4}}.
